    <item>
      <title>Making A Scene</title>
      <link>https://mezpahlan.github.io/blog/2017/04/16/making-a-scene/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 16 Apr 2017 12:26:14 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://mezpahlan.github.io/blog/2017/04/16/making-a-scene/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;For the past few weeks I&amp;rsquo;ve been taking a brief detour into the &lt;a href=&#34;https://developer.android.com/reference/android/support/transition/package-summary.html&#34;&gt;Transitions&lt;/a&gt; framework in Android. I&amp;rsquo;ve building a success screen that initially shows a full screen image and text and later transitions into a summary of your transaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;iframe src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/KZ5WGGNSVjw&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; allowfullscreen title=&#34;YouTube Video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This post documents some of the things I&amp;rsquo;ve learned whilst working on this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Deconstructing Tweets</title>
      <link>https://mezpahlan.github.io/blog/2015/07/06/deconstructing-tweets/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2015 19:25:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://mezpahlan.github.io/blog/2015/07/06/deconstructing-tweets/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;As part of my personal project for Spring, and to coincide with the UK 2015 General Election, I decided to create some bots that mirrored the main party candidates and translated their tweets to Jive. They are still running so you can find them on Twitter: &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/edjiveaband&#34;&gt;Ed Jiveaband&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/nickjivegg&#34;&gt;Nick Jivegg&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/davidjiveron&#34;&gt;David Jiveron&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure &gt;
    
    






&lt;img 
  
  sizes=&#34;(min-width: 64em) 1500px, (min-width: 58em) 1200px, (min-width: 48em) 800px, (min-width: 38em) 500px, 500px&#34;
  
  srcset=&#39;
  
    /blog/2015/07/06/deconstructing-tweets/deconstructing_hu4bc902ea1200feb53c4479b815cc2f4a_659800_500x0_resize_box_2.png 500w
  
  
  
  &#39;
  src=&#34;https://mezpahlan.github.io/blog/2015/07/06/deconstructing-tweets/deconstructing.png&#34; 
  
  alt=&#34;&#34;
  
&gt;

    &lt;figcaption&gt;Deconstructing Tweets&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the more interesting problems that I faced was how to prevent special Tweet Entities being erroneously translated by the Jive translator. You may be asking what is a Tweet Entity? Let me explain about them first and then go on to explain how I can tackle such a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
